cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC 

This paper focuses on the use of BERT for non-factoid question-answering, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores learning-to-rank setups, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), and discusses coping with large passages, which falls under the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
